<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3989] Groovy compiler allows overriding final methods but class loading fails with java.lang.VerifyError</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3989</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The following script compiles but when run, class loading fails saying &quot;java.lang.VerifyError: class B overrides final method&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;A {
    def foo() {}
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; def bar() {}
}
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;B &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;extends&lt;/span&gt; A {
    def foo() {}
    def bar() {}
}
B
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If I swap the order of method definitions in class B as:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;A {
    def foo() {}
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; def bar() {}
}
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;B &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;extends&lt;/span&gt; A {
    def bar() {}
    def foo() {}
}
B
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;then it correctly gives the error message &quot;You are not allowed to overwrite the final method bar() from class &apos;A&apos;.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
